gomodel:SYNGO_4026  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5C: Bath application of the mGlu2/3 receptor agonist DCG-IV induces an inward current in voltage-clamped WT CA3 pyramidal cells. DCG-IV failed to induce significant current in CA3 pyramidal cells from RTN4 KO (Nogo-A-/- ) or mGlu3-/- mice indicating that RTN4 might be downregulating mGlu3 receptor activity in CA3 pyramidal cells of Nogo-A-/- mice.\n\nqPCR studies did not demonstrate a reduction of Grm3 transcript levels in the cells.\n\nThe term 'synaptic signalling via neuropeptide' was used because of the lack of evidence that RTN4 induces an allosteric modulation of mGluR2/3 receptor.\n\nA similar experimental paradigm was conducted to check for modulation of mGlu2 receptors in dentate granule cells. Loss of RTN4 did not affect mGlu2 receptor activity in CA3 pyramidal cells.. Experimental description: RTN4 KO (Nogo-A-/- ) mice were bred as described in Gähwiler et al, 1997 (PMID: 9347615)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4026" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

